  "texts": [
    "It is very critical to train a GAN in a way that both models train in a balanced state during the whole training time.",
    "One solution is to reach a Nash equilibrium.",
    "It is very difficult to reach Nash equilibrium in practice.",
    "The issue is that a GAN sticks to the saddle point where the objective function gives minimal weight parameters for one model while the maximal weight parameters are for the other model.",
    "However, a minimax game can be used to find a Nash equilibrium."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}